The paper discusses the use of neural networks to approximate the Bellman operator, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of "deep learning" or "reinforcement learning." This suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with stochastic approximations and set-valued maps, which are topics that fall under the categories of "stochastic systems" (cs.SY) and "optimization and control" (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the convergence of the algorithm, which is a topic in "artificial intelligence" (cs.AI) and "neural and evolutionary computing" (cs.NE).
